<TEXT>
   ``Black Rain,'' the thriller starring Michael
Douglas as a cop who tracks a killer through the streets of Japan,
captured first place in box office revenues last weekend.
   The Paramount movie grossed $9.7 million in its first three days
of release.
   Universal's ``Sea of Love,'' the romantic suspense tale
featuring Al Pacino in his first film since the 1985 bomb
``Revolution,'' collected $7.8 million to land in second place.
