<FIRST>r a PM-TVGuideEditor     09-26 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-TV Guide Editor,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Robinowitz Named National Editor at TV Guide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RADNOR, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Joe R. Robinowitz, general manager of WFXT-TV
in Boston and former editor of the Boston Herald, has been named
national editor of TV Guide.
   ``I'm delighted to be back in print journalism, particularly
with such a prestigious magazine, which brings both worlds
together,'' Robinowitz said.
   The appointment was announced Monday by News America Publishing
Inc., the Rupert Murdoch company that bought TV Guide from Walter
H. Annenberg last year. The weekly has two co-editors, one for
national coverage and one for local sections.
   Robinowitz, 38, succeeds David Sendler, who resigned Sept. 14
over what he said were editorial differences with Murdoch.
   Robinowitz was assistant managing editor in charge of developing
a Sunday newspaper for the New York Post and, from 1982 to 1986,
was editor of the Herald.
   Murdoch owns the Herald, agreed last week to sell WFXT and owned
the Post until last year.
   TV Guide is the most widely read magazine in the nation, with
circulation estimated by Robinowitz at 16 million a week.
</TEXT>
