<HEAD>Argentine President to Meet With Bush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Argentine President Carlos Menem will meet
with President Bush at the White House on Wednesday, Press
Secretary Marlin Fitzwater announced today.
   Menem is in the United States to attend the United Nations in
New York and will stop by for a visit with Bush.
   Bush will commend the new Argentine president for his efforts to
deal with his nation's economic problems, and the two are also
expected to discuss the drug issue, trade and the regional peace
efforts in Central America, Fitzwater said.
