<FIRST>u i AM-Duarte     09-26 0224</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Duarte,0232</SECOND>
<HEAD>Former President Duarte Suffers Relapse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former President Jose Napoleon
Duarte, who is dying of liver cancer, was in stable condition
Tuesday after suffering another relapse, according to his doctors.
   ``Duarte is on oxygen and suffering from fever,'' said Dr. Jose
Luis Saca.
   Duarte, 63, came down with pneumonia last week but responded to
treatment with antibiotics.
   He was taken to a private hospital Tuesday for lung X-rays and
other examinations.
   Duarte's son Alejandro told photographers that his father ``has
had a relapse but the relapse is not serious. He is breathing
normally, he is conscious and apparently has a lung problem.''
   Saca said Duarte will be transferred to Walter Reed Military
Hospital in Washington for a checkup in about 10 days ``when his
general condition improves.''
   He said the trip would be made to evaluate the cancer and decide
whether to resume chemotherapy.
   ``We doctors here consider that there is no need to give him
more chemotherapy because the cancer is no longer being
controlled,'' Saca said.
   When doctors at Walter Reed diagnosed Duarte's cancer in June
1988 they removed 60 percent of his stomach and found that the
disease had invaded his liver.
   Last June 1, Duarte became the first elected president of El
Salvador to turn his office over to another elected president.
</TEXT>
