<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--Krol     09-26 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Krol,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Retired Archbishop Goes Home From Hospital After Surgery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Roman Catholic Cardinal John Krol left St.
Agnes Hospital Tuesday, a week after surgery to remove fluid from
his brain.
   Krol, 78, left the hospital in good condition and good spirits,
according to St. Agnes spokesman Bob Gallagher.
   The retired archbishop of Philadelphia was admitted to St. Agnes
Hospital Sept. 19 and was transferred to Graduate Hospital that
night for the operation.
   On Saturday, he returned to St. Agnes Hospital, where his
personal physician, Dr. Joseph Gambescia, is on the staff.
   Gallagher said Krol's operation was very similar to one
performed recently on former President Reagan.
   Krol served as archibishop of Philadelphia from 1961 to 1988.
</TEXT>
