<HEAD>Angry Motorists Trap Reckless Trucker, Hold Him for Police</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: RECASTS lede to CLARIFY that police now saying truck not forced
off road but boxed in at truckstop. CORRECTS time element in 2nd graf;
RECASTS 5th graf, `When the...' to CONFORM and CORRECTS charge in last
graf.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHAZY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Motorists got so fed up with a reckless
driver that they took matters into their own hands, boxing in his
truck at a truckstop and holding him until police arrived.
   A tractor-trailer rig was weaving in and out of traffic Sunday
on the Adirondack Northway near the town of Chazy, tailgating and
nearly running some cars off the road, said Trooper Kevin Triller.
   After several miles, five motorists _ all strangers _ pulled
over, discussed the situation and decided to act, Triller said.
   One went to summon police while the other four sped northward
and caught up with the truck just south of the Canadian border.
   When the truck exited the highway and drove to a nearby
truckstop, the motorists boxed in the truck and kept the driver,
Rene Fortier, 31, of Mercier, Quebec, until police arrived and
arrested him.
   The motorists and their passengers, about 10 people in all, then
went to Champlain Town Court to file charges. Fortier pleaded
guilty to speeding and was fined $217, Triller said.
</TEXT>
