<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The military imposed heavy security on
the Caribbean tourist city of Cartagena today after another bomb
blast blamed on drug traffickers killed two people and injured one
at a Hilton hotel.
   Two other bombs exploded Monday, injuring one other person.
   Today, a Cabinet minister was to meet with representatives of
the country's 4,600 judges in an effort to head off a strike in
protest of what the judges call the government's failure to
adequately protect them from drug gangs.
   Colombian marines, army troops and national police patrolled
