showed surprising strength in new factory orders for durable goods.
   The Commerce Department reported that factory orders for ``big
ticket'' durable items such as cars, airplanes and machinery, rose
3.8 percent in August, the biggest advance this year. The market
had expected a slight decline.
   Despite the overall strength in today's market, Wall Street
analysts said it still lacked strong leadership.
   ``There's no firm conviction,'' said Emmanuel Geronimous. ``The
market could swing either way.''
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
up 1.22 to 192.50.
   On the American Stock Exchange, the market value index was 1.28
higher at 382.68.
